@startuml Terminal Event Handling - Input Processing

title Terminal Event Handler - Event Mapping and Processing

package "Event Polling and Mapping" {
    class EventHandler {
        ---
        + new() -> Self
        + poll_event(timeout: Duration) -> Result<Option<TerminalEvent>>
        - map_event(event: Event) -> TerminalEvent
        - map_key_event(key: KeyEvent) -> TerminalEvent
        - map_mouse_event(event: MouseEvent) -> TerminalEvent
    }

    note right of EventHandler
        Abstraction layer over crossterm events.
        Maps platform-specific events to
        custom TerminalEvent enum.

        Windows-specific:
        - Filters Release and Repeat events
        - Only processes Press events
        - Prevents duplicate input

        Cross-platform:
        - Keyboard mapping consistent
        - Mouse wheel support
        - Resize events handled
    end note
}

package "Key Event Mapping" {
    state KeyEventMapping {
        state Modifiers <<choice>>

        [*] --> FilterKind

        state FilterKind {
            note right of FilterKind
                WINDOWS FIX: Check KeyEventKind
                - Release -> Unknown
                - Repeat -> Unknown
                - Press -> continue
            end note
        }

        FilterKind --> Modifiers

        state Modifiers {
            note right of Modifiers
                Match (code, modifiers):
                - CONTROL+C -> CtrlC
                - CONTROL+L -> ClearScreen
                - Modifier combinations
                - Shift for uppercase
            end note
        }

        state MatchByCode {
            code --> Enter: "TerminalEvent::Submit"
            code --> Backspace: "TerminalEvent::DeleteChar"
            code --> Tab: "TerminalEvent::TabComplete"
            code --> "Up (no mod)": "TerminalEvent::HistoryPrevious"
            code --> "Down (no mod)": "TerminalEvent::HistoryNext"
            code --> "Left": "TerminalEvent::MoveCursorLeft"
            code --> "Right": "TerminalEvent::MoveCursorRight"
            code --> "PageUp": "TerminalEvent::ScrollUp"
            code --> "PageDown": "TerminalEvent::ScrollDown"
            code --> "Ctrl+Up": "TerminalEvent::ScrollUp"
            code --> "Ctrl+Down": "TerminalEvent::ScrollDown"
            code --> "Char(c)": "TerminalEvent::InputChar(c)"
            code --> Other: "TerminalEvent::Unknown"
        }

        Modifiers --> MatchByCode

        Enter --> [*]
        Backspace --> [*]
        Tab --> [*]
        HistoryPrevious --> [*]
        HistoryNext --> [*]
        MoveCursorLeft --> [*]
        MoveCursorRight --> [*]
        ScrollUp --> [*]
        ScrollDown --> [*]
        InputChar --> [*]
        Unknown --> [*]
    }
}

package "Mouse Event Mapping" {
    class MouseEventMapping {
        ScrollUp -> TerminalEvent::ScrollUp
        ScrollDown -> TerminalEvent::ScrollDown
        ---
        LeftMouseButton + Down
          -> MouseDown { column, row }
        LeftMouseButton + Drag
          -> MouseDrag { column, row }
        LeftMouseButton + Up
          -> MouseUp
        ---
        RightMouseButton or other
          -> Unknown
    }

    note right of MouseEventMapping
        Only left mouse button events.
        Right-click and others ignored.

        Used for scrollbar interaction:
        - MouseDown on scrollbar column
        - MouseDrag to drag thumb
        - MouseUp to finish drag

        Scroll wheel: separate events
        for smooth scrolling
    end note
}

package "TerminalEvent Enum" {
    class TerminalEvent {
        <<enum>>
        ---
        InputChar(char)
        Submit
        DeleteChar
        MoveCursorLeft
        MoveCursorRight
        HistoryPrevious
        HistoryNext
        ScrollUp
        ScrollDown
        TabComplete
        ClearScreen
        CtrlC
        Quit
        Resize(u16, u16)
        MouseDown { column: u16, row: u16 }
        MouseDrag { column: u16, row: u16 }
        MouseUp
        Unknown
    }

    note right of TerminalEvent
        Input Events:
        - InputChar(c): regular character
        - Submit: Enter pressed
        - DeleteChar: Backspace

        Navigation Events:
        - MoveCursorLeft/Right: arrow keys
        - HistoryPrevious/Next: up/down
        - ScrollUp/Down: page/ctrl+arrow
        - TabComplete: Tab key

        Control Events:
        - CtrlC: Ctrl+C
        - ClearScreen: Ctrl+L
        - Quit: application exit
        - Resize(w, h): terminal resized

        Mouse Events:
        - MouseDown/Drag/Up: button events
        - ScrollUp/Down: wheel events

        Error/Fallback:
        - Unknown: unmapped event
    end note
}

package "Event Handling Flow in main.rs" {
    note as MainLoop
        Main event loop flow:

        1. event_handler.poll_event(timeout)
           -> Option<TerminalEvent>

        2. Match on TerminalEvent:
           - InputChar: insert in InputBuffer
           - Delete: delete from InputBuffer
           - MoveCursor: update cursor position
           - History: navigate history
           - Scroll: update OutputBuffer scroll
           - Submit: process input command
           - Mouse: calculate scrollbar position
           - Resize: trigger reflow
           - CtrlC: context-aware cancel
           - Quit: exit loop

        3. terminal_ui.render(state)
           -> Renders updated state

        4. Repeat until Quit event
    end note
}

package "Context-Aware Event Handling" {
    note as ContextAware
        Events interpreted differently
        based on TerminalMode:

        NORMAL MODE:
        - InputChar: add to input buffer
        - Submit: submit command to classifier
        - HistoryPrevious/Next: navigate history
        - Scroll: move output view

        EXECUTING_COMMAND:
        - CtrlC: cancel command with SIGINT
        - InputChar: buffered but not executed

        WAITING_LLM:
        - CtrlC: cancel LLM query
        - Spinner animates independently

        AWAITING_COMMAND_APPROVAL:
        - 'y' / 'Y': approve command
        - 'n' / 'N': reject command
        - Ctrl+C: cancel approval

        AWAITING_ANSWER:
        - InputChar: build answer text
        - Submit: send answer to LLM
        - Backspace: edit answer

        AWAITING_MORE_INPUT (multiline):
        - InputChar: continue input
        - Submit: finalize if complete
        - Ctrl+C: cancel multiline
    end note
}

package "Key Binding Reference" {
    class KeyBindings {
        Ctrl+C: CtrlC (context-aware)
        Ctrl+L: ClearScreen
        Ctrl+Arrow Up: ScrollUp
        Ctrl+Arrow Down: ScrollDown
        ---
        Enter: Submit
        Backspace: DeleteChar
        Tab: TabComplete (not impl)
        ---
        Arrow Up (no Ctrl): HistoryPrevious
        Arrow Down (no Ctrl): HistoryNext
        Arrow Left: MoveCursorLeft
        Arrow Right: MoveCursorRight
        ---
        Page Up: ScrollUp
        Page Down: ScrollDown
        ---
        Char (a-z,0-9, symbols): InputChar
        Shift+Char: InputChar (uppercase)
        ---
        Mouse Scroll: ScrollUp/Down
        Mouse Click (left): MouseDown
        Mouse Drag (left): MouseDrag
        Mouse Release (left): MouseUp
    }

    note right of KeyBindings
        Character input:
        - NONE or SHIFT modifiers only
        - Other modifiers -> Unknown

        Navigation:
        - Arrow keys without Ctrl
          -> history navigation
        - Arrow keys with Ctrl
          -> scroll output

        Special:
        - Some commands suspend TUI
          (vim, nano, less, etc)
        - Event polling paused
          during suspension
    end note
}

package "Platform Considerations" {
    note as Windows
        WINDOWS SPECIFIC HANDLING:

        Crossterm generates multiple events
        per keystroke on Windows:
        - KeyEventKind::Press (initial)
        - KeyEventKind::Repeat (held down)
        - KeyEventKind::Release (released)

        Solution: Filter in map_key_event()
        Only process KeyEventKind::Press

        Result: Single event per keystroke
        No duplicate input handling needed
    end note

    note as Linux
        LINUX/MAC SPECIFIC:

        Single event per keystroke
        No filtering needed

        Interactive commands work:
        - suspend() -> vim/nano
        - resume() -> back to terminal

        Event polling paused during
        interactive command to prevent
        input conflicts
    end note
}

package "Mouse Scrollbar Interaction" {
    note as ScrollbarInteraction
        Mouse events used for scrollbar:

        1. User clicks scrollbar
           -> MouseDown event
           -> Get ScrollbarInfo.column
           -> Check if click on scrollbar

        2. User drags on scrollbar
           -> MouseDrag events
           -> ScrollbarInfo.row_to_scroll_position()
           -> Update OutputBuffer.scroll_position()

        3. User releases mouse
           -> MouseUp event
           -> Finalize scroll position

        ScrollbarInfo calculated during
        render_frame() so mouse coordinates
        map correctly to content
    end note
}

note bottom
    ARCHITECTURE HIGHLIGHTS:

    1. ABSTRACTION: TerminalEvent enum
       hides platform differences

    2. WINDOWS COMPATIBILITY: Filters
       Release/Repeat events for single input

    3. CONTEXT-AWARE: Same event
       handled differently per mode

    4. SIMPLE MAPPING: KeyCode+Modifiers
       -> TerminalEvent direct match

    5. MOUSE SUPPORT: Scrollbar and
       scroll wheel fully integrated

    6. RESIZE HANDLING: Terminal size
       changes detected and processed

    7. EXTENSIBLE: Easy to add new
       events without changing core logic
end note

@enduml
